## 1. Objective

The objective of this product is to design and develop a **clean, modern, and responsive LMS portal** that allows learners to easily access courses, study materials, assessments, and progress tracking across **web and mobile devices**.

The platform should support multiple course categories such as **Soft Skills, Technical Skillsets, Aptitude Training, and Other Courses**, while providing a scalable navigation system for future expansion.

---

## 2. Target Users

### Primary Users

* College students
* Job seekers / placement preparation candidates
* Early career professionals

### Secondary Users

* Trainers / instructors
* Admins / content managers

---

## 3. Key User Goals

* Quickly access enrolled courses
* Resume learning from the last completed lesson
* Navigate modules and lessons with minimal friction
* Track progress, assessments, and certificates
* Seamlessly switch between mobile and web

---

## 4. Platform Scope

### In Scope

* Web (Desktop & Tablet)
* Mobile Web & Mobile App (Android / iOS)
* Student-facing dashboard

### Out of Scope (Phase 1)

* Instructor course creation panel
* Advanced analytics dashboard

---

## 5. Information Architecture

### 5.1 Global Sidebar Navigation (Primary Navigation)

This sidebar is persistent across the platform and serves as the main navigation.

**Menu Items:**

1. Dashboard
2. My Courses
3. Course Library
4. Learning Path / Roadmap
5. Assessments
6. Resources
7. Discussions / Doubts
8. Announcements
9. Profile
10. Settings / Help

**Behavior:**

* Collapsible on web
* Icon-only collapsed state
* Hidden behind hamburger menu on mobile

---

### 5.2 Course-Level Sidebar (Contextual Navigation)

Displayed only when a user enters a specific course.

**Menu Items:**

* Course Overview
* Modules (Expandable)
* Lessons
* Assignments
* Quizzes & Tests
* Downloads
* Discussion (Course-specific)
* Notes

**Behavior:**

* Accordion-based module navigation
* Highlights current lesson
* Displays completion indicators
* Collapsible on web, slide-in drawer on mobile

---

## 6. Dashboard Requirements

### 6.1 Student Dashboard

**Components:**

* Welcome message
* Continue Learning card
* Enrolled courses overview
* Progress summary
* Upcoming assessments
* Announcements

---

## 7. Course Structure

### Course Card Attributes

* Course title
* Category
* Rating
* Duration
* Number of modules
* Enrollment count
* Progress status

### Course Content Types

* Video lessons
* Reading materials
* PDFs / Downloads
* Practice exercises
* Quizzes
* Assignments

---

## 8. Mobile Responsiveness Requirements

### Navigation

* Bottom navigation bar for:

  * Home
  * Courses
  * Progress
  * Profile

* Hamburger menu for secondary items

### Course View

* Swipeable module list
* Sticky "Continue / Next Lesson" CTA
* Optimized video player for mobile

---

## 9. UI / UX Guidelines

* Clean, minimal design
* Card-based layouts
* Soft shadows and rounded corners
* Consistent spacing and typography
* Color-coded course categories
* Clear progress indicators

---

## 10. Functional Requirements

### Must Have

* User authentication
* Course enrollment
* Progress tracking
* Resume learning functionality
* Assessment attempts
* Certificate generation

### Nice to Have

* Bookmark lessons
* Offline downloads (mobile)
* Dark mode
* Global search

---

## 11. Non-Functional Requirements

* Responsive across all screen sizes
* Fast load time (< 3s)
* Scalable navigation structure
* Secure content access
* Accessibility compliant (WCAG basics)

---

## 12. Success Metrics

* Course completion rate
* Daily active users (DAU)
* Average session duration
* Assessment participation rate
* User satisfaction score

---

## 13. Risks & Considerations

* Navigation complexity with many courses
* Content scalability
* Mobile performance for video content

---

## 14. Future Enhancements

* Instructor dashboard
* AI-based course recommendations
* Advanced analytics
* Gamification (badges, streaks)

